Interface Dao<K,T extends Entity>

  • Type Parameters:
    K - the type of id
    T - the type extends Entity
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    BitmapDao, CartDao, CommentDao, ItemDao, OrderDao, QuestionDao, UserDao
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    BitmapDaoImpl, CartDaoImpl, CommentDaoImpl, ItemDaoImpl, OrderDaoImpl, QuestionDaoImpl, UserDaoImpl

    public interface Dao<K,T extends Entity>
    The interface Data Access Object (Dao) to abstract and encapsulate all access to the data source. The DAO manages the connection with the data source to obtain and store data. The DAO implements the access mechanism required to work with the data source
    Author:
    Sergei Chmut.
